"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The seaborn documentation states that the rc argument in set_style() function should only override parameters that are part of the style definition. However, 'grid.color' and 'grid.linewidth' are not part of the style definition in seaborn. They are part of the matplotlib parameters. Therefore, you should use the higher-level set_theme() function or the axes_style() function to customize these parameters.\",\n  \"patch\": \"8c8\\n< sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_theme(rc=scale_dict)\\n\\n14c14\\n< sns.set_style(rc=style_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n> sns.axes_style(rc=style_dict)\"\n}"